%% Data Flow Diagram: llama-stack-k8s-operator
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Platform Admin
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Operator as LlamaStackDistribution<br/>Reconciler
    participant Kustomize as Kustomize Renderer
    participant LlamaServer as Llama Stack Server<br/>8321/TCP HTTP
    participant IngressCtrl as Ingress Controller<br/>80/443 TCP
    participant Client as External Client

    Note over User,LlamaServer: Flow 1: LlamaStackDistribution Reconciliation

    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply LlamaStackDistribution CR
    K8sAPI->>Operator: Watch event (CR created/updated)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS, SA token
    Operator->>Kustomize: Render manifests from base templates
    Kustomize-->>Operator: Rendered Deployment, Service,<br/>NP, PVC, HPA, PDB, SA, RB
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create/Update resources<br/>443/TCP HTTPS, SA token
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: Resources created
    Operator->>LlamaServer: GET /v1/health<br/>8321/TCP HTTP plaintext
    LlamaServer-->>Operator: Health status
    Operator->>LlamaServer: GET /v1/version<br/>8321/TCP HTTP plaintext
    LlamaServer-->>Operator: Version info
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Update CR status<br/>443/TCP HTTPS, SA token

    Note over User,LlamaServer: Flow 2: ConfigMap-Triggered Reconciliation

    User->>K8sAPI: Update user ConfigMap<br/>(referenced by CR)
    K8sAPI->>Operator: ConfigMap watch event<br/>443/TCP HTTPS, SA token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Find referencing CRs<br/>(field indexer lookup)
    K8sAPI-->>Operator: Matching CRs
    Operator->>Kustomize: Re-render manifests
    Kustomize-->>Operator: Updated manifests
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Apply updated resources<br/>443/TCP HTTPS, SA token

    Note over Client,LlamaServer: Flow 3: External Client Access (exposeRoute enabled)

    Client->>IngressCtrl: HTTP/HTTPS request<br/>80/443 TCP
    IngressCtrl->>LlamaServer: Forward to service<br/>8321/TCP HTTP plaintext
    LlamaServer-->>IngressCtrl: Response
    IngressCtrl-->>Client: Response
